<docs>
	<doc for="PropertyValueChangedEventArgs.PropertyValueChangedEventArgs">
		<summary>
			<para>Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.PropertyValueChangedEventArgs"/>class.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="changedItem">The item in the grid that changed. </param>
		<param name="oldValue">The old property value. </param>
	</doc><doc for="PropertyValueChangedEventArgs.ChangedItem">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.GridItem"/> that was changed.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>A <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.GridItem"/> in the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.PropertyGrid"/>.</para>
		</value>
	</doc><doc for="PropertyValueChangedEventArgs.OldValue">
		<summary>
			<para>The value of the grid item before it was changed.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
   A object representing the old value of the property.
</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>This property provides you with the value of the
      property as it was before the change was applied. You can find the new value by
      querying the property grid with the specified <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.PropertyValueChangedEventArgs.ChangedItem"/>. </para>
		</remarks>
	</doc><doc for="PropertyValueChangedEventArgs">
		<summary>
			<para>Provides data for the <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.PropertyGrid.PropertyValueChanged"/> event of a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.PropertyGrid"/> .</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>The <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.PropertyGrid.PropertyValueChanged"/>
event occurs when the user changes the value of a property, which is
specified as a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.GridItem"/>
, in a <see cref="System.Windows.Forms.PropertyGrid"/>.</para>
			<para>For more information about handling events, see
<see topic="cpconEventsOverview"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
	</doc></docs>
